Emir of Bauchi, Alhaji Rilwanu Adamu, on Sunday, urged  youths in the state to acquire various skills in order to become self-reliant. Adamu, who gave the advice at his end of Eid-el-Fitr Sallah celebration message in Bauchi, also advised them to engage in meaningful endeavours that would dignify them and the society at large. “By engaging in the numerous and various skill acquisitions, you will meet up with the manpower demands, become self-reliant and be employers,” he said. (NAN)